SIMPLE: performance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Performance
<hw>Per*form"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
performing; the carrying into execution or action; execution;
achievement; accomplishment; representation by action; <as>as, the
<ex>performance</ex> of an undertaking of a duty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Promises are not binding where the <qex>performance</qex> is
impossible.</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is performed or accomplished; a thing
done or carried through; an achievement; a deed; an act; a feat; esp.,
an action of an elaborate or public character.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Her walking
and other actual <xex>performances</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧His musical <xex>performances</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Macaulay.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Completion; consummation; execution;
accomplishment; achievement; production; work; act; action; deed;
exploit; feat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Performer</ent>⟦br⟧
